raries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/spacesvr/spacesvr\">Spaces VR</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/spacesvr/spacesvr\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">123</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":123,\"repo\":\"spacesvr/spacesvr\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A front end framework for quickly creating VR websites built on react-three-fiber.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T07:59:46.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Web3XR</h2><h3>Galleries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://glry.xyz/\">glry.xyz</a> - A site that hosts virtual galleries for NFT art on the Tezos blockchain.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T07:28:19.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Audio</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://beats.gatunes.com/\">beats</a> - A semi-collaborative app with various rooms where anyone can create or modify an existing musical loop.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T07:02:43.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Audio</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cybrxr.com/\">Cybr</a> - Offers a platform for live immersive listening parties. The recorded portions of their first listening party are still available to view.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T07:02:43.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Audio</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.letsfathom.com/vr/play\">Fathom VR</a> - A WebXR version of the music discovery app Fathom, which lets you search for and explore clouds of related artists with spatialized audio.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T07:02:43.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Audio</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.helicon.live/\">Helicon</a> - An immersive introduction to polyrhythms.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T07:02:43.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Audio</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://demos.littleworkshop.fr/track\">TRACK</a> - A linear ride through an immersive audiovisual experience developed by <a href=\"https://www.littleworkshop.fr/\">Little Workshop</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T07:02:43.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Avatars</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://readyplayer.me/\">ReadyPlayerMe</a> - Lets you quickly and easily create a 3D avatar online that you can download in glTF format.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:09:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Art</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://brushworkvr.com/\">Brushwork VR</a> - A VR app that simulates the process of painting with a virtual canvas, palette, color mixing, and more.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Art</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.silkbrush.app/\">Silk Brush</a> - A port of Tilt Brush to WebXR with plans for future extensions.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Avatars</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://vroid.com/en\">VRoid</a> - Lets you create anime-styled 3D avatars that export to the highly-compatible .vrm format.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Forums</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://discourse.threejs.org/\">three.js Forum</a> - Official three.js forum.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Forums</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://forum.playcanvas.com/\">PlayCanvas Forum</a> - Official PlayCanvas forum.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Communities</h2><h3>Reddit</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/WebVR/\">r/WebVR</a> - Initially the main subreddit for WebVR discussion, now features general WebXR content along with <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/WebXR/\">r/WebXR</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Content Hubs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://2wsz.com/\">2WSZ</a> - An aggregator for WebXR content featuring ratings, a recommendation system, and both English and Korean language support.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Content Hubs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://constructarcade.com/\">Construct Arcade</a> - A curated hub of WebXR games, with games from both outside developers and in-house developers at Vhite Rabbit.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Content Hubs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://xrswim.com/\">XR Swim</a> - An aggregator site for both WebXR and Web3 content.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Content Hubs</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://xrsites.com/\">XRSites</a> - An aggregator for WebXR games and experiences.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development</h2><h3>Frameworks and Libraries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://aframe.io/\">A-Frame</a> - Lets you create VR experiences using declarative HTML and custom JavaScript components built on top of three.js.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://aframe.io/docs/\">Official Documentation</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development</h2><h3>Frameworks and Libraries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jbaicoianu/janusweb\">JanusWeb</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jbaicoianu/janusweb\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">144</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":144,\"repo\":\"jbaicoianu/janusweb\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - An in-browser implementation of JanusVR that lets you build social VR experiences.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development</h2><h3>Frameworks and Libraries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://lovr.org/\">LÖVR</a> - A Lua-based framework that lets you create VR content across web and native platforms.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://lovr.org/docs/\">Official Documentation</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development</h2><h3>Frameworks and Libraries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://p5xr.org/\">p5.xr</a> - An add-on for the library p5.js that allows you to create immersive p5 sketches.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development</h2><h3>Frameworks and Libraries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://threejs.org/\">three.js</a> - A JavaScript library for rendering 3D content with WebGL that powers many existing WebXR experiences and tools.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://threejs.org/docs/index.html#manual/en/introduction/Creating-a-scene\">Official Documentation</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Social Spaces</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dreamwave.tech/\">Dreamwave</a> - A web-based platform for hosting scalable virtual events. Powered the virtual music festival <a href=\"https://dreamwave.tech/secret-sky-2021\">Secret Sky 2021</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Social Spaces</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://hubs.mozilla.com/\">Hubs</a> - Mozilla's platform for enabling users to gather and collaborate virtually.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Web3XR</h2><h3>Realms</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://vrland.io/\">vrland</a> - A platform for gathering and virtual showcases that supports displaying of NFTs.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T06:08:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Web3XR</h2><h3>Realms</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://somniumspace.com/parcel/\">Somnium Space Web</a> - A web viewer that allows you to explore parcels from <a href=\"https://www.somniumspace.com/\">Somnium Space</a> in your browser, with VR support on the Oculus Quest browser.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T05:42:48.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Standout Projects</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://moonrider.xyz/\">Moonrider</a> - A rhythm game built by Supermedium similar to Beat Saber.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T04:46:03.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-a-frame\">Learn A-Frame (VR)</a> - A roughly 6-hour Codecademy course written in partnership with A-Frame.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T04:33:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Learning Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://doc.babylonjs.com/guidedLearning\">babylon.js Guided Learning</a> - Detailed text and video tutorials that complement the other instructional pages in the documentation.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T04:33:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Social Spaces</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://framevr.io/\">FRAME</a> - A platform focused on enabling easy 3D collaborations in a virtual space.</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T02:21:52.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development</h2><h3>Other</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.soft8soft.com/verge3d/\">Verge3D</a> - A toolkit that allows 3D artists to export their scenes and create immersive web experiences with ease.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.soft8soft.com/support-documentation/\">Official Documentation</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T02:01:36.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development</h2><h3>Engines</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://godotengine.org/\">Godot</a> - A cross-platform, open-source engine with WebXR support as of version 3.2.4.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.godotengine.org/en/stable/classes/class_webxrinterface.html\">Official Documentation</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T01:49:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development</h2><h3>Engines</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.nunustudio.org/\">nunuStudio</a> - A multiplatform, open-source engine built on three.js that can be used natively or in the browser.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.nunustudio.org/docs/\">Official Documentation</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T01:49:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development</h2><h3>Engines</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://playcanvas.com/\">PlayCanvas</a> - A browser-based WebGL engine with support for WebXR content, mobile browsers, collaborative editing, and more.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.playcanvas.com/en/\">Official Documentation</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T01:49:14.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Development</h2><h3>Engines</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://unity.com/\">Unity</a> - A highly popular game engine with community packages that enable content to be exported for WebXR.\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/De-Panther/unity-webxr-export\">WebXR Export</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/De-Panther/unity-webxr-export\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">587</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":587,\"repo\":\"De-Panther/unity-webxr-export\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Exporter by <a href=\"https://github.com/De-Panther/\">De-Panther</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Rufus31415/Simple-WebXR-Unity\">SimpleWebXR</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Rufus31415/Simple-WebXR-Unity\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">450</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":450,\"repo\":\"Rufus31415/Simple-WebXR-Unity\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Exporter by <a href=\"https://github.com/Rufus31415\">Rufus31415</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2021-08-04T01:49:14.000Z"}]},"previous":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/dersvenhesse/awesome-scriptable","repo":"dersvenhesse/awesome-scriptable"},"next":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/osmlab/awesome-openstreetmap","repo":"osmlab/awesome-openstreetmap"}},"pageContext":{"repo":"msub2/awesome-webxr","id":"awesomes/github.com/msub2/awesome-webxr","previousId":"awesomes/github.com/dersvenhesse/awesome-scriptable","nextId":"awesomes/github.com/osmlab/awesome-openstreetmap"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","2828988102"]}